==Overview==
Statwise, a pumped up version of the [[Pirate]] [[Brigantine]], the Akuma is a lightly shielded but fast and powerful destroyer with a curious weapon layout. Sporting less anti-capital weaponry than other battleships but far more anti fighter weaponry also, it can fend off massed fighters better than most battleships. Quite a bit more expensive than comparable Commonwealth destroyers.

==Background==
===Encyclopedia Entry===
The recently-introduced Akuma destroyer, as its name suggests, is considered a demon among the innocent pilots trying to get safely to their destination. Little is known about the capabilities of this ship.

==Physical Characteristics==
The Akuma bears a passing resemblance to the [[Ryu]], except with a longer fuselage with a small section connecting the bow to the large stern. It bears forward-facing spikes reminiscent of Teladi ships.
== Combat ==
With 8 slots in its up/down turrets, the Akuma absolutely shreds fighters and corvettes. Its anti-capital broadsides are not lacking but its forward turret is, with only 4 guns, meaning it is least dangerous from the front - unlike others in its class. A loadout trick to further improve its fighter defence is the 'ionised flak' in its up/down mounts. With some flak weapons and some [[Ion Disruptor]]s, it can extend the range of the IDs considerably, damaging enemy ships' shields constantly as it fires.

